# 10. iwconfig

## Purpose

Used for configuring and managing wireless network interfaces in Linux.

## Syntax

```bash
iwconfig
```

## What It Shows

- Wireless adapter information
- SSID
- Signal strength
- Wireless mode
- Frequency

## Use Cases

- Wireless troubleshooting.
- Wi-Fi configuration.
- Signal monitoring.

---

# 11. ss (Socket Statistics)

## Purpose

`ss` is a modern replacement for netstat and provides detailed socket information.

## Syntax

```bash
ss
```

## Common Examples

```bash
ss -t
ss -u
ss -l
ss -a
```

## What It Displays

- TCP sockets
- UDP sockets
- Listening services
- Active network connections

## Benefits

- Faster than netstat.
- More detailed output.
- Better performance on large systems.

