# 15. ARP

## Purpose

ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) command is used to view and manage the ARP cache.

## Syntax

```bash
arp -a
```

## What It Displays

- IP addresses
- Corresponding MAC addresses
- ARP table entries

## Why It Matters

ARP maps Layer 3 IP addresses to Layer 2 MAC addresses.

## Use Cases

- Identifying devices on a network.
- Troubleshooting communication issues.
- Investigating ARP-related attacks.

---

# 16. ifplugstatus

## Purpose

Checks whether a network cable is physically connected to a network interface.

## Syntax

```bash
ifplugstatus
```

## What It Shows

- Link detected
- Link not detected
- Interface status

## Use Cases

- Troubleshooting physical connectivity.
- Diagnosing cable issues.

