# 19. watch

## Purpose

`watch` repeatedly executes a command and displays updated output.

## Syntax

```bash
watch <command>
```

## Example

```bash
watch netstat
```

or

```bash
watch -n 5 top
```

## What It Does

- Refreshes command output automatically.
- Monitors changing values in real time.

## Use Cases

- Monitoring processes.
- Watching network connections.
- Tracking system performance.

---

# 20. Nmap

## Purpose

Nmap (Network Mapper) is one of the most powerful network discovery and security auditing tools.

## Syntax

```bash
nmap <target>
```

## Example

```bash
nmap 192.168.1.1
```

## Features

- Host discovery
- Port scanning
- Service detection
- OS fingerprinting
- Network mapping

## Use Cases

- Asset discovery.
- Vulnerability assessments.
- Security auditing.
- Network reconnaissance.
